ublication boundary and permissions model are clearer.\n\n## Server-Side Metadata Fetch\n\nFor public v1, the Forge server should be able to create an Agent Trail snapshot\non demand by fetching GitMeta metadata for the repository referenced by the PR\nURL.\n\nExample local setup:\n\n```ini\n[remote \"meta\"]\n  url = git@github.com:gitbutlerapp/gitbutler.git\n  fetch = +refs/meta/main:refs/meta/remote/main\n[TRUNCATED]\n should let a reviewer browse the related agent sessions\nin a user-friendly way.\n\nThe browsing experience should not feel like opening a raw JSON log or a giant\nchat transcript. It should feel like exploring the working history behind the\npull request.\n\nGood session browsing behavior:\n\n- show related sessions as a small list with readable labels, agent/provider,\n  capture time, and relevance reason\n- show turns within a selected session as a compact timeline\n- group records into human request, assistant response, tool call, tool result,\n  and validation blocks\n- collapse noisy tool output by default\n- highlight commands that changed files, ran tests, failed, or produced useful\n  evidence\n- make related branches, reviews, changes, files, and validation attempts easy\n  to scan\n- let the user expand exact transcript records when they need evidence\n- preserve chronological order without forcing the user to read every record\n\nThe reviewer should be able to answer:\n\n- what did the human ask?\n- what did the agent claim it did?\n- what files or areas did it touch or inspect?\n- what commands/tools ran?\n- what validation passed, failed, or was skipped?\n- what decisions, doubts, or follow-ups appeared during the work?\n\nThe UI should support both broad scanning and exact drill-down. A reviewer\nshould be able to start at the PR overview, jump into a highlighted turn, expand\nthe relevant tool call or assistant claim, then return to the overview without\nlosing context.\n\nRaw transcript records should remain available, but they should be treated as an\nevidence drawer, not the primary browsing mode.\n\n## Ranking And Highlighting\n\nThe page should rank or highlight likely relevant turns. Relevance is a product\ndecision above `but-agentlog`.\n\nGood signals:\n\n- direct review target observation\n- direct branch target observation\n- capture time near commits or PR updates\n- prompts mentioning the feature, bug, branch, or files\n- assistant claims about implementation or tests\n- tool calls that run tests, builds, formatters, or linters\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:43:43.798Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}